Here's how to handle all three requirements:

### 1. Detect Current Theme & Subscribe to Changes

```csharp
// In your App.xaml.cs constructor or OnStart:
AppTheme current = Application.Current!.RequestedTheme;
// Returns AppTheme.Light, AppTheme.Dark, or AppTheme.Unspecified

Application.Current!.RequestedThemeChanged += (s, e) =>
{
    AppTheme newTheme = e.RequestedTheme;
    Debug.WriteLine($"Theme changed to: {newTheme}");
    // Update UI, swap ResourceDictionaries, etc.
};
```

### 2. Let the User Force a Theme

```csharp
// Force dark mode regardless of OS
Application.Current!.UserAppTheme = AppTheme.Dark;

// Force light mode
Application.Current!.UserAppTheme = AppTheme.Light;

// Reset to follow system setting
Application.Current!.UserAppTheme = AppTheme.Unspecified;
```

Persist their choice with `Preferences`:

```csharp
// Save
Preferences.Set("AppTheme", "Dark");

// Restore on startup
var saved = Preferences.Get("AppTheme", "System");
Application.Current!.UserAppTheme = saved switch
{
    "Light" => AppTheme.Light,
    "Dark"  => AppTheme.Dark,
    _       => AppTheme.Unspecified
};
```

### ⚠️ Critical: Android Setup

Your `MainActivity` **must** include `ConfigChanges.UiMode` or the `RequestedThemeChanged` event won't fire — the activity restarts instead:

```csharp
[Activity(Theme = "@style/Maui.SplashTheme",
          MainLauncher = true,
          ConfigurationChanges = ConfigChanges.ScreenSize
                               | ConfigChanges.Orientation
                               | ConfigChanges.UiMode  // ← Required!
                               | ConfigChanges.ScreenLayout
                               | ConfigChanges.SmallestScreenSize
                               | ConfigChanges.Density)]
public class MainActivity : MauiAppCompatActivity { }
```

### XAML Side

Use `DynamicResource` (not `StaticResource`) so the UI updates live when themes swap:

```xml
<Label TextColor="{DynamicResource PrimaryTextColor}" />
```

Or for simple light/dark without custom dictionaries:

```xml
<Label TextColor="{AppThemeBinding Light=Green, Dark=Red}" />
```
